<br>
- Targetting/scouting: Use a 3rd person camera view to see around corners and target mobs for stuff like harmony.<br>
<br>
- Extended range: Get an ivory claw necklace (very cheap, available in the bazaar) or other extended range item for those distance harmonies and for nuking outside AE range.<br>
-- with your bow and some good arrows you can oor (out of range) many AEs<br>
<br>
- Quiver: You should have a Fleeting Quiver. They haste your bow. They have 6 arrow-only slots. Why carry just your champion, ice, and magic arrows? Fill the remaining quiver slots with some extra &quot;give-away&quot; arrows for when people bug you because they are out of arrows.<br>
<br>
- Caster mobs: Pull with your best dispel and knock out some buffs such as haste, DS, hp/ac, and rune.<br>
<br>
- Summoning mobs: Getting summoned because you did a nice big crit on the pull? Next time try a wimpy or non-magic but long range arrow or a lighter bow.<br>
<br>
- Ranger ghetto mem blur: In a kinda-nasty bind? Root and snare your pursuers and camp. Log back in safe and sound.<br>
note: many monsters will not return to their camps while snared, only stand around.<br>
<br>
- Ranger ghetto succor: In a nasty bind? Hit weaponshield and pop a thurg gate potion (easy to make, easy to get skill to make). You'll parry for 20 seconds and the thurg gate only takes 10!<br>
<br>
- Ranger port: Get a worker sledgemallet (see next tip). Smack around just about anythign with it and you're in OT, a click away from PoK just about which is a click away from many locations!<br>
<br>
- Worker Seldgemallet:<br>
&quot;The Undead Foreman in the shipyards, has a favorite gem - Jade. <br>
<br>
In return for a Jade, he will give you a hammer which is usable by All/All and randomly procces Gate: Overthere. The effect on the hammer is a proc (you must be fighting to use it), and will not work until Level 50.&quot;<br>
Use puppet strings (clickable charm item, sometimes available in the bazaar) to get the amiably faction you need. Single pull him with harmony or root/snare/camp tricks. Turn in fast though, the charm might not last long!<br>
<br>
- Unwolfed wolf bug: Use wolf form then gotf aa skill to get wolf form +atk without being a wolf (no faction modifier, no too-low-to-hit-anything, no bouncing and barking when you attack).<br>
note: also works if you wolf form while using gotf<br>
<br>
- &quot;Get rid of your stupid looking lemon with horns helm bug&quot;: Take off your helm, use wolf form, gotf, or use any other npc illusion, put on your helm, click off the illusion. Your helm is gone!<br>
note: Following this pattern you can appear in any gear you have, for example with my TV armor and a couple other junky plate pieces I can appear in full plate while remaining in my good chainmail.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rikko1>Rikko1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/24/03 3:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ranger tips</span><hr size=1> bindsight/harmony &gt; all<br>
