<br>
Scenario: Plane of Valor/East Castle Wall<br>
Out from the camp a stroll is a big rock, 3 golems spawn around it.  Harmony the three and pull the one on the far right <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>VIA CINDER JOLT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->(less resist = more aggro, yes even from jolts), and announce it.  The enchanter/shaman can open with tash/malo and you'll lose aggro quickly onto them.  Quickly poistion yourself behind the main tank a few steps and certainly away from the slower.  As long as you're far enough away you can cast Tangling Weeds and regain aggro <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>IF</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the mob has not already begun swining on the slower -- if he did, you're too late.  If not, while snaring the creature, you giving the tank a chance to jump in the way and pull aggro from you --- you never get hit.  Back out, jolt and start shooting arrows.  Who needs Virtue?<br>
<br>
Hate List already MT, Puller, Slower, puts them down to third on the list with that additive spell... if the tank is an SK or Paladin, the mob can and should be slowed before the MT actually engages.<br>
<br>
Continue the scenario and say you were burning trueshot, forgot to snare --- 0.5 second casting slows the mob down a WHOLE lot, but won't stop him.  So long as it's not resisted, you'll have time to shoot another arrow and attempt a cast on &quot;Ensnare&quot; before the mob is close enough even to the first spawn, preventing the add. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
